                                                                                            <p class="word-copy-lh-mb"><a href="https://global.upenn.edu/isss/people/daria-knurenko/"><strong>Daria Knurenko</strong></a><strong> </strong>is a sophomore at the University of Pennsylvania studying comparative literature and history of art. She grew up in Chernihiv, Ukraine, and speaks Ukrainian, English, French, German, and Russian. She translates from and into English, French, Ukrainian, and Russian, focusing on nineteenth and twentieth century poetry. She is also the editor-in-chief of&nbsp;<a href="https://doublespeakjournal.org/index.html"><em>DoubleSpeak</em></a>.</p>
